\frac{1}{x^n - 1}
\zeta
n
a_0, a_1, \ldots, a_{n-1}
 \frac{1}{x^n - 1} = \frac{a_0}{x - 1} + \frac{a_1}{x - \zeta} + \frac{a_2}{x - \zeta^2} + \ldots + \frac{a_{n-1}}{x - \zeta^{n-1}}. 
0 \leq i \leq n -1
 a_i = \lim_{x \to \zeta^{i}} \frac{x - \zeta^{i}}{x^n - 1} = \frac{1}{(\zeta^{i} - 1) \ldots (\zeta^{i} - \zeta^{i-1}) (\zeta^{i} - \zeta^{i + 1}) \ldots (\zeta^{i} - \zeta^{n - 1})}. 
a_i = \lim_{x \to \zeta^i} \frac{1}{nx^{n-1}} = \frac{\zeta^i}{n}
\sum_{i=0}^{n-1} (\zeta^i)^k = \begin{cases} n \text{ if } n | k \\ 0 \text{ otherwise} \end{cases}
\frac{1}{x - a}
\frac{P(x)}{Q(x)}
a
Q
\lim_{x \to a} \frac{(x - a) P(x)}{Q(x)} = \frac{P(a)}{Q'(a)}.
